author: TimesReporter.com staff report
title: Area college notebook for Oct. 4
text: Area college notebook for Oct. 4 News and notes on area athletes participating in college athletics. Comment Posted Oct. 5, 2015 at 12:40 AM By TimesReporter.com staff report Posted Oct. 5, 2015 at 12:40 AM Freed runs well for Rio Grande Blake Freed (Claymont) led the University of Rio Grande men’s cross country team as it posted a 34th-place finish in Friday’s All-Ohio Collegiate Championships at Cedarville University's Elvin R. King Course. The RedStorm had 520 points as a team in the 47-school field. Among the 16 NCAA Division II and NAIA schools who participated, Rio placed 11th. Freed took top honors for the RedStorm in their season-opening race two weeks ago, did the same on Friday, placing 142nd among the 663 runners on the 8k course with a time of 26:22. Also competing for Rio in the event was freshman Brody Ferris (New Philadelphia, who placed 520th in 30:09. Others • Laini Leindecker (New Philadelphia) recorded 13 kills, hitting .565 with no attack errors and posted seven digs as the University of Albany women’s volleyball team swept Hartford in three sets 25-7, 25-9, 25-18 to improve to 2-1 in America East play and 7-8 overall Sunday. • Ohio Dominican sophomore Demetrius Farmer (Dover) recorded a career-best seven tackles and forced a fumble as the Panthers beat Lake Erie 48-26, while Muskingum sophomore Mick Fishel (Dover) had nine tackles, six solo, and an interception as the Muskies fell to Baldwin-Wallace 34-28. • Maddie Bonamico (Tuscarawas Central Catholic) recorded 12 digs for the West Liberty women’s volleyball team in a 25-13, 25-23, 21-25, 25-23 setback to UVA-Wise last Friday. • Ben Lehotay (Sandy Valley) was in the top 25 with a time of 26:15 as he helped the Walsh University men’s cross country team to a ninth-place finish at the All-Ohio Meet last Friday. By TimesReporter.com staff report
